John, I hear what you are saying. As a medic, survivors guilt seems a prerequisite. The questions that many vets carry with them, &quot;What if.....&quot;.<br><br>
However, as a whole, do you regret your experiences? Do you regret rescueing all those others? Do you regret going to 'Nam and doing the best that you possibly could, within your power? How many lives saved do you attribute to your being there?<br><br>
There are many, many things that I wish I could have change. You know about the Cambodian village and me personally digging up that child from the mass grave. Do these individual experiences detract the positives which I was involve in? I don't feel so. I have come to the point that, as in life, we must accept the bad with the good.<br><br>
That's is what life is.
